# Privacy Policy — Only the Best

Last updated: June 28, 2026

## Information We Collect

**Location** — We use your device location to find restaurants near you. Location data is sent to Google Places API to perform searches and is not stored on our servers.

**Account Information** — When you sign in with Apple, we receive a unique user identifier and optionally your name and email address. This is used only to save your favorites and subscription status on your device.

**Usage Data** — We track how many searches you've used within the app to enforce free tier limits. This data is stored locally on your device.

## Third-Party Services

**Google Places API** — Used to search for restaurants. Your location is shared with Google to perform searches. Google's privacy policy applies: https://policies.google.com/privacy

**Google AdMob** — Free tier users see ads served by Google AdMob. AdMob may use your device's advertising identifier (IDFA) to show relevant ads, subject to your App Tracking Transparency choice. Google's privacy policy applies: https://policies.google.com/privacy

**Apple Sign In** — Authentication is handled entirely by Apple. We do not receive your Apple ID password.

## Data Storage

Your favorites and preferences are stored locally on your device using iOS standard storage. We do not operate a backend server or database.

## Your Choices

- You can revoke location access at any time in iOS Settings → Only the Best → Location.
- You can opt out of ad tracking via iOS Settings → Privacy & Security → Tracking.
- You can delete your account from the app's Settings screen, which removes all locally stored data.

## Children

This app is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect data from children.

